{% comment %}
  RALJE — Meet the Makers
  Rahul Soni (Founder, Designer) and Jay (Master of Manufacturing)
{% endcomment %}

<!-- Chapter Header -->
<section class="chapter-header">
  <p class="chapter-header__label reveal">The Makers</p>
  <h1 class="chapter-header__title reveal">THE HANDS</h1>
  <p class="chapter-header__subtitle reveal">Two makers. One standard. Two continents.</p>
</section>

<!-- Rahul Soni -->
<section class="page-section section--bone">
  <div class="atelier-container">
    <div class="maker-profile">
      <div class="maker-profile__image reveal">
        {{ 'rahul-soni-portrait.jpg' | asset_url | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', alt: 'Rahul Soni — Founder of RALJE' }}
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="maker-profile__role reveal">Founder · Fourth-Generation Goldsmith</span>
        <h2 class="maker-profile__name reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">RAHUL SONI</h2>
        <hr class="atelier-divider reveal">
        <div class="maker-profile__bio">
          <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
            Rahul is the fourth generation of the Soni family's goldsmithing lineage, rooted in Rajasthan — the historical centre of jewelled arts on the subcontinent. From age ten, he worked beside his father on a Rajasthani bench, first repairing silver, then moving into the full range of traditional work.
          </p>
          <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
            In 2017, he came to the United States. Over three years, he added the disciplines the traditional workshop could not teach: three-dimensional modelling, photorealistic rendering, the ability to show a client a piece that does not yet exist, in the light it will wear.
          </p>
          <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
            Today, every RALJE piece begins in Southern California, where Rahul designs the jewellery — consulting with the client, developing the concept in 3D, rendering the piece in photorealistic detail for approval.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Divider Quote -->
<section class="page-section section--ink" style="padding: var(--space-xl) 0;">
  <div class="atelier-container text-center">
    <blockquote class="reveal" style="border: none; text-align: center; padding: 0; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <p>The hands that make the piece are the same hands that have always made the piece — they are simply on two continents now.</p>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Jay -->
<section class="page-section section--bone">
  <div class="atelier-container">
    <div class="maker-profile maker-profile--reversed">
      <div class="maker-profile__image reveal">
        {{ 'jay-workshop-portrait.jpg' | asset_url | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', alt: 'Jay — Master of Manufacturing' }}
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="maker-profile__role reveal">GIA-Certified · Master of Manufacturing</span>
        <h2 class="maker-profile__name reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">JAY</h2>
        <hr class="atelier-divider reveal">
        <div class="maker-profile__bio">
          <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
            Jay is a GIA-certified master of manufacturing who oversees every stage of the physical creation: sourcing, casting, setting, finishing, and quality inspection.
          </p>
          <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
            Depending on the type of jewellery and the techniques required, the piece is made in Gujarat, Rajasthan, or Mumbai — wherever the specific craft expertise is strongest.
          </p>
          <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
            This is not outsourcing. Jay is family. The workshop is RALJE's own. The completed piece returns to Rahul for final review, marking, and delivery.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- How We Work Together -->
<section class="page-section section--parchment">
  <div class="atelier-container atelier-prose">
    <h3 class="reveal">How RALJE Works Today</h3>
    <hr class="atelier-divider reveal">
    <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
      Every RALJE piece begins in Southern California, where Rahul designs the jewellery — consulting with the client, developing the concept in 3D, rendering the piece in photorealistic detail for approval.
    </p>
    <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
      The approved design, along with complete diamond and material specifications, is then sent to Jay in India for manufacturing.
    </p>
    <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
      The completed piece returns to Rahul for final review, marking, and delivery.
    </p>
    <div class="text-center mt-xl">
      <a href="/pages/commission" class="atelier-btn atelier-btn--gold reveal">Begin a Conversation</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
